    {
        "content": "<p>This would not work as it would complain it can't infer the field <code>ùïú</code>. Also, what is <code>x</code>? You use it as a new identifier and also in the statement <code>HasDerivAt $f _ x</code>. Also what would be the use case for this? If a function expects <code>HasDerivAt</code> then you can just call <code>fun_prop</code> directly. I can imagine one would like to transform <code>fderiv ùïú f x</code> into the actual derivative and that would require more meta code.</p>",
